contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

13:03.308 --> 13:05.309
- (beeps)
- There we go.

13:05.310 --> 13:07.620
I know it's been you
cyberbullying me.

13:07.621 --> 13:09.122
I didn't mean
to get you expelled,

13:09.123 --> 13:10.814
but now I'm glad I did.

13:10.815 --> 13:13.200
You're a very disrespectful
young lady.

13:13.201 --> 13:14.943
At least <i> I'll</i> have a paper towel

13:14.944 --> 13:17.237
with the power
to take on any spill.

13:17.238 --> 13:18.447
Okay, that's it.

13:18.448 --> 13:20.041
You'll pay for this, Connie!

13:20.042 --> 13:23.660
You better watch your step.

13:23.661 --> 13:24.928
(gasping and murmuring)

13:29.501 --> 13:31.627
Ah, darn it. I couldn't open
my camera in time.

13:31.628 --> 13:33.837
Oh, you can just text me yours.

13:33.838 --> 13:36.565
I'm not texting you.
I don't know you.

13:39.636 --> 13:41.804
Peter, I'm exhausted.

13:41.805 --> 13:43.564
I can't even think
of making dinner.

13:43.565 --> 13:45.182
Well, I didn't hear
what you just said,

13:45.183 --> 13:46.734
but what's the dinner situation?

13:46.735 --> 13:48.736
¶ ¶

13:48.737 --> 13:51.572
<i>Good evening, I'm Tom Tucker,</i>
<i>transitioning into my sad voice</i>

13:51.573 --> 13:53.240
<i>for the death of a white girl.</i>

13:53.241 --> 13:56.002
<i>Local white girl Connie D'Amico</i>
<i>died at the scene</i>

13:56.003 --> 13:58.195
<i>of an automobile accident</i>
<i>earlier tonight,</i>

13:58.196 --> 14:01.174
<i>the brake lines of Connie's</i>
<i>Celica apparently cut.</i>

14:01.175 --> 14:03.492
Oh, my God. How horrible!

14:03.493 --> 14:05.661
(exhales)
Can you imagine being the shovel

14:05.662 --> 14:08.831
that gets to scrape that ass
off the road?

14:08.832 --> 14:11.291
Eh, maybe in my next life.

14:11.292 --> 14:12.017
(knock on door)

14:13.336 --> 14:16.505
Lois Griffin, I'm sorry,
but you're under arrest.

14:16.506 --> 14:19.174
I'm gonna have to take you down
to the station.

14:19.175 --> 14:20.843
On what charge?

14:20.844 --> 14:22.603
We've got you
on grocery store video

14:22.604 --> 14:24.179
threatening Connie D'Amico.

14:24.180 --> 14:26.032
You're under arrest
for her murder.

14:26.033 --> 14:27.558
What?!

14:27.559 --> 14:30.945
Guys, my mom was arrested
for Connie's murder.

14:30.946 --> 14:32.896
No quiz!

14:32.897 --> 14:34.331
(all cheering)

14:44.325 --> 14:45.742
Joe, this is ridiculous.

14:45.743 --> 14:47.536
There's no way
Lois killed Connie.

14:47.537 --> 14:49.204
There's just too much evidence
against her.

14:49.205 --> 14:50.631
I got to take her in.

14:50.632 --> 14:52.875
So, what, I'm supposed to be
a guy without a wife now?

14:52.876 --> 14:55.728
What am I supposed to do,
whatever I want whenever I want?

14:55.729 --> 14:58.064
I'm gonna get crow's-feet
from smiling too much.

14:58.065 --> 15:00.424
Sorry, Peter. It's gonna be
quite an adjustment.

15:00.425 --> 15:02.885
Seriously, who's gonna greet me
in a shapeless sweatshirt

15:02.886 --> 15:04.887
- when I come home?
- Meg, maybe.

15:04.888 --> 15:07.431
Who's gonna slap a tarantula
of shampoo hair

15:07.432 --> 15:08.765
on the wall of the shower?

15:08.766 --> 15:10.225
It's the little things you miss.

15:10.226 --> 15:12.486
Who's gonna go, "Ooh! Ooh!
Careful!" while I'm parking?

15:12.487 --> 15:14.989
Sometimes this is
the hardest part of my job.

15:14.990 --> 15:17.900
Who's gonna fill up my DVR
with lady judge programs?

15:17.901 --> 15:19.326
I-I don't make the rules.

15:19.327 --> 15:21.829
Oh, and I suppose now I'll have
to start every road trip

15:21.830 --> 15:24.331
- with a full tank of gas?
- I took an oath, Peter.

15:24.332 --> 15:26.667
What am I supposed to do?
Masturbate comfortably in bed?

15:26.668 --> 15:28.076
The law's the law.

15:28.077 --> 15:30.454
And I guess I'm gonna have to be
on time to every party

15:30.455 --> 15:32.840
- and stay real late?
- Yeah, why do they do that?

15:32.841 --> 15:35.083
And so long,
<i>Handmaid's Tale,</i> I guess.

15:35.084 --> 15:36.844
Two or three more jokes, Peter.

15:36.845 --> 15:38.179
So long,<i> This Is Us.</i>

15:38.180 --> 15:39.346
Last one, maybe.

15:39.347 --> 15:41.256
So long, seeing my dining room.

15:41.257 --> 15:42.633
You got a stronger one
to end on?

15:42.634 --> 15:45.093
So long,
bitchy 2:00 a.m. blanket pulls.

15:45.094 --> 15:46.446
Ah, there we go.

15:46.447 --> 15:48.989
(bleep), Peter.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.267
What am I supposed to do now,
Brian?

15:52.268 --> 15:54.195
Whatever I want whenever I want?

15:54.196 --> 15:56.271
Yeah, I was right here
when you were doing that.

15:56.272 --> 15:58.482
Oh.
I-I didn't hear your laugh.

15:58.483 --> 16:00.375
I'm more of a smile guy.

16:04.155 --> 16:06.490
Peter, we have got to prove
Lois is innocent.

16:06.491 --> 16:08.375
That's right.
And the best way to crack

16:08.376 --> 16:10.327
any high-profile crime case

16:10.328 --> 16:13.288
is to do a podcast
before you have all the facts.

16:13.289 --> 16:15.290
- Okay.
- And the key to any podcast

16:15.291 --> 16:18.126
is poor sound quality
and tons of commercials.

16:18.127 --> 16:19.720
All right, we've got Lois
calling in from prison.

16:19.721 --> 16:21.481
She's only got three minutes.

16:21.482 --> 16:23.483
<i>LOIS (staticky):</i>
<i>Thanks for looking</i>
<i>at my case, guys.</i>

16:23.484 --> 16:25.392
You bet, Lois.
My first question is...

16:25.393 --> 16:27.177
do you get a good night's sleep?

16:27.178 --> 16:30.231
<i>No, 'cause I'm in prison,</i>
<i>and my cellmate is bipolar.</i>

16:30.232 --> 16:32.349
Well, if you get
a Casper mattress now,

16:32.350 --> 16:34.017
you have a hundred days
to decide

16:34.018 --> 16:35.477
if it's the right mattress
for you.

16:35.478 --> 16:37.163
<i>Peter,</i>
<i>I don't have time for this.</i>

16:37.164 --> 16:39.165
I don't have time
for underwear that bunches up.

16:39.166 --> 16:41.858
That's why I wear MeUndies.
Perfect underwear

16:41.859 --> 16:43.577
for hanging yourself
in your jail cell.

16:43.578 --> 16:46.339
<i>Can we talk about the case?</i>
<i>I have 30 seconds</i>

16:46.340 --> 16:48.841
<i>before they haul me off</i>
<i>to the freaking cafeteria.</i>

16:48.842 --> 16:50.751
Sounds like
you could use Blue Apron.

16:50.752 --> 16:53.370
Have you ever wanted to receive
a vegetable in the mail?

16:53.371 --> 16:54.922
Then you need Blue Apron.

16:54.923 --> 16:56.832
I'm, like, obsessed
with the stir-fry.

16:56.833 --> 16:59.001
Brian here
likes the Moroccan beef.

16:59.002 --> 17:01.837
I-I have no opinion
on the Moroccan beef, Peter.

17:01.838 --> 17:04.006
Brian, this is not art.
This is commerce.

17:04.007 --> 17:06.174
<i>Peter, before I go,</i>
<i>I need a new lawyer.</i>

17:06.175 --> 17:08.361
<i>This one made</i>
<i>a sexual pass at me.</i>

17:08.362 --> 17:10.863
Oh, boy. Everyone knows
hiring is a nightmare.

17:10.864 --> 17:12.940
At least it was
before ZipRecruiter.

17:12.941 --> 17:16.059
ZipRecruiter:
we vastly overestimate

17:16.060 --> 17:19.579
how many podcast listeners are
in a position to hire someone.

17:22.784 --> 17:24.526
Okay, Brian,
let's go through Lois's drawers

17:24.527 --> 17:26.878
and look for clues.
If you find any, let me know.

17:26.880 --> 17:29.031
And if you find
the yo-yo she took from me,

17:29.032 --> 17:30.716
definitely let me know.

17:30.717 --> 17:31.884
Stupid Lois.

17:31.885 --> 17:33.460
I'm not gonna use it
in the house.

17:33.461 --> 17:35.370
The Wendy's employee
gave it to me

17:35.371 --> 17:36.872
if I promised to calm down.

17:36.873 --> 17:38.206
Peter, this is a dead end.

17:38.207 --> 17:40.393
All I see here is your Nerf gun
from last summer.

17:40.394 --> 17:42.803
Oh, no way.
She said I lost that.

17:42.804 --> 17:45.139
She deserves to be in jail.

17:45.140 --> 17:46.140
PETER:
Hey!

17:46.141 --> 17:47.883
Suck on that, Lois!

17:47.884 --> 17:49.977
That was very close
to my eyes, Peter.

17:49.978 --> 17:51.645
It wasn't close to your eye.

17:51.646 --> 17:54.781
- That's why I took it.
- It was so far from your eye.

17:58.102 --> 17:59.320
What are we doing here?

17:59.321 --> 18:01.080
Connie never went
to the Drunken Clam.

18:01.081 --> 18:03.732
Doesn't matter. Everybody knows
the way you solve a murder

18:03.733 --> 18:05.901
is to ask a barkeep
if he knows anything.

18:05.902 --> 18:07.661
When he says no,
you turn around,

18:07.662 --> 18:10.447
and then he says "wait"
and gives you an important clue.

18:10.448 --> 18:13.283
Hey, Jerome, do you know
anything about Connie's death?

18:13.284 --> 18:15.836
No, man.
I've just been working here.

18:15.837 --> 18:17.412
All right, Brian.
Let's get out of here.

18:17.413 --> 18:19.340
- Peter, wait.
- Yes?

18:19.341 --> 18:22.584
One of the waitresses says
you put her tip down her pants.

18:22.585 --> 18:26.013
Huh. How long were you planning
to sit on that little nugget?

18:26.014 --> 18:27.422
You just did it.

18:27.423 --> 18:28.515
Okay, Jerome.

18:28.516 --> 18:30.425
If you <i> remember</i> anything else,

18:30.426 --> 18:33.279
here's my number.

18:33.280 --> 18:36.197
Oh, and here's a nickel
for the watered-down beer.

18:37.618 --> 18:39.576
Keep the change.

18:43.290 --> 18:45.124
How are we gonna solve
this case, Peter?

18:45.125 --> 18:46.292
I've been thinking about that.

18:46.293 --> 18:48.819
You're a dog,
and I'm a man. Right?

18:48.820 --> 18:50.278
So we're basically <i> Scooby-Doo.</i>

18:50.279 --> 18:52.322
- So, what are you saying?
- We go around town

18:52.323 --> 18:55.450
and rip off faces
until we find the real killer.

18:55.451 --> 18:56.877
Unless...

18:56.878 --> 18:58.995
(screams)

18:58.996 --> 19:00.714
Which can only mean...

19:00.715 --> 19:02.332
(screams)

19:02.333 --> 19:04.334
Twins? Guess again.

19:04.335 --> 19:06.061
(both scream)

19:15.805 --> 19:18.823
The newspaper
is embarrassing me.

19:23.571 --> 19:25.665
Well, kids, we tried.

19:25.666 --> 19:27.908
I'm afraid
your mother's a murderer.

19:27.909 --> 19:30.026
No, Peter, I'm right here.

19:30.027 --> 19:31.578
Lois, you escaped!

19:31.579 --> 19:33.488
Careful, kids.
She killed before.

19:33.489 --> 19:35.866
- She'll kill again.
- JOE: No, Peter, look wider.

19:35.867 --> 19:37.510
We're all here.

19:37.511 --> 19:39.178
Turns out
Lois didn't kill anyone.

19:39.179 --> 19:41.514
Connie D'Amico
faked her own death.

19:41.515 --> 19:43.257
- (all gasp)
- Gasp!

19:43.258 --> 19:46.018
We found Connie an hour ago
at a motel outside of town.

19:46.019 --> 19:48.262
Turns out she put a pig
in a blonde wig

19:48.263 --> 19:49.747
behind the wheel of her car.

19:49.748 --> 19:53.100
I'm sorry, our coroner
has been pretty sloppy lately.

19:53.101 --> 19:55.635
She's been dealing
with some substance abuse.

19:55.636 --> 19:57.938
"She"?
Interesting.

19:57.939 --> 20:00.223
Anyway, Lois has been cleared
of all charges.

20:00.224 --> 20:01.725
And what of the pig?

20:01.726 --> 20:04.160
That was a very tough
house call.

20:08.232 --> 20:10.617
- Yes?
- Excuse me, folks.

20:10.618 --> 20:12.286
Do you have a daughter
named Peppa?

20:12.287 --> 20:13.879
Yes.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.256
You're gonna want to sit down.

20:23.056 --> 20:24.465
Well, Lois, I got to say,

20:24.466 --> 20:26.225
it's great to have you home
from prison.

20:26.226 --> 20:27.709
Ah, it's great to be home.

20:27.710 --> 20:29.252
Hey, I-I got to ask,

20:29.253 --> 20:31.213
are-are you gonna stay
that jacked forever?

20:31.214 --> 20:32.565
I don't know.
Do you like it?

20:32.566 --> 20:35.309
I-I-I do and I don't, you know?

20:35.310 --> 20:37.928
It-it was... it was nice
being held up against a wall,

20:37.929 --> 20:41.223
but when you made me suck
the hairdryer, I-I...

20:41.224 --> 20:42.633
I enjoyed it, I did,

20:42.634 --> 20:45.560
but I-I don't want to do
that specific thing again.

20:45.561 --> 20:47.729
Well, that's too bad,
'cause I'm ready for round two.

20:47.730 --> 20:50.123
Just got to make sure
the kids don't come in.

20:53.110 --> 20:54.945
- (whimpers)
- Now no one can get in,

20:54.946 --> 20:56.422
and no one can get out.

20:56.423 --> 20:58.073
Hands on the headboard, chief.

20:58.074 --> 20:59.591
Yes, ma'am.

